</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Replace the M&amp;C-scanner.
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref href="GUID-563F9EBE-CC03-4CAA-93C8-8AA3AB9B162B.xml" class="- topic/xref " type="task"><?ditaot gentext?>05 How to remove the Measurement &amp; Control (M&amp;C) unit</xref>
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-FEAE8DCA-C235-453F-AB84-89976B0A6B67" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Evaluate/Prevention</b> </title><p class="- topic/p ">Maintain the M&amp;C-scanner as described in the Care&amp;Use-poster.
</p></section><section id="GUID-45E72CCA-32F0-41FD-ACF2-4A4D42D55C79" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Background info</b></title><p class="- topic/p ">When the patterns of the test-chart for the self-test of the M&amp;C-scanner are not measured correctly this error is raised. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In most case this is caused by a polluted scanner or patterns that are not printed correctly.
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-480B4E14-7AB9-4230-BBE2-97A999EC3E19.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Diagnostics</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
